for col in categorical_cols:
    if col == "Occupation":
        continue
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
    sns.histplot(data=df, x=col)
    plt.title(f'{col} distribution by Occupation')
    plt.xlabel(col)
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

In [ ]:

Importance of Skewness in data:¶

Understanding positive skew in your numeric columns gives you real behavioral or financial insights into how the population is distributed — especially useful in risk analysis, customer profiling, and financial planning¶

What Does a Positively Skewed Distribution Mean?¶

  • Has a long tail on the right (high values are rare)
  • Most data points are clustered at the lower end
  • A small number of records have very high values
In [ ]:

Insights for Each of Numeric Columns¶

1️⃣ Estimated Income → Positively Skewed¶

📌 Insight: Most people in the dataset have lower income levels, and only a few earn very high incomes. 💡 Use: Useful for identifying high-income outliers or segmenting premium customers.

2️⃣ Superannuation Savings (Retirement Savings)¶

📌 Insight: Majority have small retirement savings, while a few have saved a lot. 💡 Use: Indicates need for financial advisory services or targeted saving campaigns.

3️⃣ Credit Card Balance¶

📌 Insight: As you correctly noted — most people have low balances, and only a few carry large debts. 💡 Use: Helps identify high-risk credit users vs. low-risk ones.

4️⃣ Bank Loans¶

📌 Insight: Most customers have no or small loans, a few have taken large loans. 💡 Use: Can signal risk exposure or need for loan-based segmentation.

5️⃣ Bank Deposits¶

📌 Insight: Most people have low deposit amounts, with a few high-net-worth individuals (HNWIs). 💡 Use: Opportunity to target big savers for investment products.

6️⃣ Checking Accounts¶

📌 Insight: Majority have small balances in checking accounts. 💡 Use: Could reflect day-to-day spenders vs. those who keep large liquidity.

7️⃣ Saving Accounts¶

📌 Insight: Most have modest savings, and only a few save heavily. 💡 Use: Indicates potential for financial growth products or auto-savings tools.

8️⃣ Foreign Currency Account¶

📌 Insight: Most users either don’t use or hold very small foreign currency, few hold a lot. 💡 Use: Target those few for forex trading, NRI banking, or international funds.

9️⃣ Business Lending¶

📌 Insight: Very few have taken business loans; those who did took large amounts. 💡 Use: Indicates low business lending penetration — potential area for growth.
